column2: loons nested on island this year
baby loon agg was gone from nest. I think an animl destroyed it. No baby again this year.
June 9- two baby loons were born

column1: End of July one was missing- one survived

column2: Noticed three beavers throughout the month of August playing in the water. I have not seen this in the last six years.

It rained for 8 days. Finally got out and noticed that the lake was an awful thick pea-green color. Took the clarity test and it was 7 ft. I have never seen the clarity of the lake at this depth. I talked to a couple that have been on the lake for 29 years- they have never seen the lake this green before.
Sunny- light breeze- cool (under 50 degrees)- no boats on lake- lake very green- did not see the loons- milfoil was treated early August 2007- Dave Blumer of DNA and Mike Stachowiak assisted.

On October 6 my husband and son were out on our pontoon and they watched 3 beavers for a couple hours and noticed them chewing on trees and they were dropping in the water and the beavers took the branches and brought them down the lake to build their yearly dam on the NW corner of the lake.
Partly cloudy and windy; no boats on lake; temp 60 degrees
One baby loon was born early this month and survived the summer.
No boats on lake; breezy; partly cloudy; lake treated for milfoil 1 day prior
sunny- breezy- no boats on lake- loons near bay- treated lake for Eurasian Milfoil about 2 weeks ago.

I thought the milfoil was the worst year yet since discovery in 2003. But it did not mat up half as bad as in previous years.  It was a very short summer.
